docs.snippet: Tenants who were driven out by an urban renewal project that stalled for decades are hard to track down.

headline.main: Trying to Undo a Lower East Side Diaspora

docs.abstract: Tenants displaced by Lower East Side redevelopment that began in 1967 say city's 50-year-old promise of priority for apartments when project is completed should stand; reopening soon on razed site, Essex Crossing complex offers 1,000 units, half permanently affordable; advocates argue city owes special debt to former residents of this lost community and should help them return home.
